Package: glockr
Title: Count Lines of Code Using 'scc'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", email = "mjfrigaard@pm.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: An R wrapper around the 'scc' (Succinct Code Counter) command-line
    utility <https://github.com/boyter/scc>. Counts lines of code, comments,
    and blank lines across many languages, with optional complexity metrics.
    'scc' must be installed and available on the system PATH.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    processx,
    jsonlite,
    tibble
Suggests:
    ggplot2,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    tidyr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
SystemRequirements: scc (https://github.com/boyter/scc)
URL: https://github.com/mjfrigaard/glockr
